VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> FEDU_CORR_ERROR - Estimate of the percent error in the corrected electron flux.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Dimension 0 holds 8011 time bins. Dimension 1 corresponds to 11 pitch angle bins.  Dimension 2 holds 25 energy bins. The percent error is defined as a relative error: d(Flux)/Flux*100%, where Flux is the corrected flux.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Lstar - Roederer's generalized L-shell parameter. Computed for 90deg. particles using OP77Q external field and IGRF internal field.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: L-shell parameters are dimensionless.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> L - McIlwain's L-shell parameter. Computed for 90deg. particles using OP77Q external field and IGRF internal field.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: L-shell parameters are dimensionless.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> I - Integral invariant. Computed for 90deg. particles using OP77Q external field and IGRF internal field.
---> B_Calc - Magnitude of computed model field at the S/C. Computed using OP77Q external field and IGRF internal field.
---> B_Eq - Magnitude of computed model field at the Minimum-|B| point along the field line threading the S/C. Computed using OP77Q external field and IGRF internal field.
---> MLT - Eccentric Dipole Magnetic Local Time. Computed using OP77Q external field and IGRF internal field.
---> MLAT - Eccentric Dipole Magnetic Latitude. Computed using OP77Q external field and IGRF internal field.
---> Position - Geocentric Geocentric position in Re.
---> LstarVsAlpha - Roederer's generalized L-shell parameter. Pitch angle depenedent (pitch angles are local pitch angles). Computed using OP77Q external field and IGRF internal field.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: L-shell parameters are dimensionless.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> Alpha values for LstarVsAlpha variable. I.e., they are the local pitch angles that L* is computed for in LstarVsAlpha. Units are degrees.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Alpha values for LstarVsAlpha variable.
